## Fork Workflow

This project is a fork of `{{ fork_upstream }}`.

### Remote structure

- `upstream` — `{{ fork_upstream }}` (source of truth)
- `origin` — your fork (set by you: `git remote add origin <your-fork-url>`)

### Syncing with upstream

```bash
git fetch upstream
git merge upstream/{{ fork_upstream_branch }}
```

### Keeping template files up to date

```bash
copier update
```

### Contributing back

1. Sync with upstream
2. Create a feature branch: `git checkout -b feat/my-change`
3. Commit and push to your fork: `git push origin feat/my-change`
4. Open a Pull Request from your fork to upstream
